results.question: Is Brooklyn rich or poor?
results.title: Brooklyn Facts
results.snippet: One in five Brooklyn households has a median income of over $100,000 per year—twice as many as a decade before—while one in five receives food stamp benefits. Brooklyn ranks first in NYC in total number of children living in poverty. Five of the 10 poorest NYC census tracts are in Brooklyn.

results.question: What is Brooklyn known for?
results.title: Brooklyn, NY Guide Including Things to Do and Where to Eat - Time Out
results.snippet: If Brooklyn were its own city like it used to be, it would be the third-most populous one in the country. However, the area is definitely worth discovering for it is the home of iconic New York attractions like Coney Island, the Brooklyn Bridge and Prospect Park, plus some of the best New York pizza.Nov 12, 2021

results.question: Is Brooklyn NY A nice place to live?
results.title: 9 Essential Tips for Living in Brooklyn, New York - CubeSmart
results.snippet: Brooklyn Is Excellent for Families Families living in Brooklyn, New York will find the walkable sidewalks, peaceful parks, sense of community, and family-friendly activities ideal for family life. From the Brooklyn Children's Museum to the Prospect Park Zoo, there are plenty of activities for children in Brooklyn.

results.question: Did Brooklyn used to be a city?
results.title: Brooklyn - Wikipedia

What’s happening in Brooklyn? 😳

The @TheCrossover staff breaks down the Nets’ situation with Kevin Durant and Kyrie Irving trib.al/vmMX5aA

With a top talent like Kevin Durant available, teams will be throwing trade offers left, right and centre to bring him to their team. @GoldieOnSports discusses the top candidates for a potential Durant swap with the Brooklyn Nets.

www.sportsnet.ca/art…

Andre Drummond played for the Brooklyn Nets with Kevin Durant. 

We wanted to learn a lesson from the “Chicago White Sox signing Manny Machado’s brother in law and best friend” incident but here we are. 

👀

Brooklyn has no incentive to tank, but they also have no reason to worry about their record, either. That undercuts the threat from Durant and Kyrie of refusing to play if they're not traded. So what? The season's toast anyway. Get the offer you want. AK
The nets falling apart is the knicks fans championship I get it, Brooklyn forever though.
Kevin Durant Requests Trade From Brooklyn Nets hypebeast.com/2022/6…

On @GEICO SportsNite, @IanBegley joins @mmargaux8 on day one of NBA free agency to talk about what the Knicks expect with signing Jalen Brunson, what to expect from Isaiah Hartenstein, what's next for the Knicks, and how we got to Kevin Durant asking to be traded from Brooklyn
nets fans trying to keep KD & kyrie from leaving brooklyn

If you’re Brooklyn, you kinda have to do a Kyrie/Russ deal if it’s on the table right? 

Rewind back a couple years I’m honestly shocked the Lakers gave up so much for AD when everyone knew he wanted out and where he wanted to go. 

Brooklyn doesn’t have any leverage. Sit Kyrie?
Brooklyn Nets star Kevin Durant has reportedly listed the Phoenix Suns as a preferred trade destination.  www.rappler.com/spor…

I speak for ALL Nets fans when I say we REALLY want this duo in Brooklyn 🔥
